            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ". Even the name of “America’s sports car” was geared at those who had served in the military. Revealed at the 1953 Motorama, people clamored for the new car and GM scrambled to make a first run of 300.",
