            "text": "Just as amazing is how GM assembly workers dressed to assemble the Corvettes. Frist off, they’re in getups which look more like what you’d expect a soda fountain employee to wear, but that was the mode of the time. Secondly, they were wearing minimal protective gear like masks and gloves. Working with fresh fiberglass and the other materials used in the process without much ",
